  "extraHighlightWords": [],
  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "On the last day before summer vacation, Mr. Pan played a game instead of a normal lesson: he called out a word, and we had to use it in a sentence about our own year.",
      "zh": "暑假前的最後一天，潘老師沒上正常的課，改玩了一個遊戲：他念出一個字，我們就要用那個字造一句跟自己這一年有關的句子。"
    },
    {
      "en": "He started with \"marry,\" and Bernice immediately shouted, \"My aunt is going to marry a man who works in media!\" which was, at least, completely true.",
      "zh": "他先出了「marry」，Bernice 馬上大喊：「我姑姑要嫁給一個在媒體業工作的男人！」這句話至少是完全真實的。"
    },
    {
      "en": "For \"wife,\" a boy said his uncle's future wife plans to move to the northern part of the country after the wedding.",
      "zh": "輪到「wife」，有個男生說他叔叔未來的太太計劃婚後搬到國家的北部。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mr. Pan gave us \"forget,\" and I said I would never forget my very first diary entry, back on the first day of school.",
      "zh": "潘老師出了「forget」，我說我永遠不會忘記自己第一篇日記，就是開學第一天寫的那篇。"
    },
    {
      "en": "For \"tire,\" William's teacher apparently said a similar game happened at his school, and he answered that giant robots never get tired, only their batteries do.",
      "zh": "輪到「tire」，聽說 William 學校也玩了類似的遊戲，他回答巨大機器人永遠不會累，只有電池會沒電。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Someone got \"dirty\" and simply pointed at William's shoes from the farm field trip months ago, and the whole class laughed.",
      "zh": "有人拿到「dirty」，直接指了指幾個月前農場校外教學時 William 那雙鞋，全班都笑了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "For \"kill,\" a boy said this year's math homework nearly killed his motivation completely, which felt relatable to most of us.",
      "zh": "輪到「kill」，有個男生說今年的數學作業差點徹底殺死他的動力，這句話讓我們大部分人都心有戚戚焉。"
    },
    {
      "en": "I got \"eraser,\" and I mentioned I went through at least ten of them this year, mostly because of math mistakes.",
      "zh": "我拿到「eraser」，我說我今年至少用掉了十個橡皮擦，大部分都是因為數學錯誤。"
    },
    {
      "en": "For \"file,\" Bernice said she finally organized her school papers into one single file instead of one giant messy pile.",
      "zh": "輪到「file」，Bernice 說她終於把學校的紙本整理成一個檔案夾，而不是一大堆亂七八糟的紙。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Someone used \"legal\" by saying it becomes legal to get a part-time job once you turn a certain age, which sparked a small debate about fairness.",
      "zh": "有人用「legal」造句，說到了一定年紀打工才合法，這引發了一場關於公不公平的小小辯論。"
    },
    {
      "en": "For \"medical,\" I mentioned our school health check-up, and how my medical card said \"healthy, active, good posture.\"",
      "zh": "輪到「medical」，我提到我們學校的健康檢查，還有我的醫療卡上寫著「健康、活潑、姿勢良好」。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mr. Pan gave us \"poor\" and \"rich,\" and one girl said a diary makes you feel rich in memories, even on days you feel poor in everything else.",
      "zh": "潘老師出了「poor」跟「rich」，有個女生說日記能讓你在回憶上感覺很富有，就算其他方面感覺很貧乏的日子也一樣。"
    },
    {
      "en": "For \"self,\" I said keeping this diary all year taught me more about my own self than any single test ever did.",
      "zh": "輪到「self」，我說寫這整年的日記，讓我對自己的認識比任何一次考試都還要多。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Someone got \"shake\" and described shaking hands with the museum guide during our old town field trip, which felt very grown-up at the time.",
      "zh": "有人拿到「shake」，描述了老城區校外教學時跟博物館導覽員握手的事，當時感覺自己超成熟。"
    },
    {
      "en": "For \"shower,\" William apparently told his teacher that after every soccer practice, a cold shower feels like the best part of the whole day.",
